article.headline: Winthrop 65, Coker 50
article.story: ROCK HILL, S.C. (AP) -- Torrell Martin scored 18 points to lead Winthrop to a 65-50 victory against Coker Saturday night. Winthrop trailed 28-27 at halftime but held Coker to seven point in the first 12 minutes of the second half to build a 49-34 lead. The Eagles (2-1) led by as many as 21 with just under five minutes remaining when Billy Houston scored inside to give Winthrop a 61-40 lead. Coker (2-2) closed out the game with a 10-4 run as Jason Fulwood drilled back-to-back 3-pointers. The Cobras finished the game at 50 percent on 17 of 34, while the Eagles connected on 47 percent (24-51). Coker was limited by Winthrop's second half pressure defense to just 12 field goals.
